title: Research provides insight on survivability of rare Wyoming plant

title_detail.value: Research provides insight on survivability of rare Wyoming plant

summary: New research has found that despite the low density of the desert yellowhead -- there are fewer than 15,000 individual plants scattered across just 55 acres -- these populations survive partly because of a principle called negative density dependence.
